Preconditions:
The input linked lists l1 and l2 must not be empty.
Each node in the linked lists must contain a single digit.
The most significant digit should be at the beginning of the linked lists.

Postconditions:
The method should return a linked list representing the sum of the two input linked lists.
The sum should be calculated by adding the corresponding digits from the two linked lists.
If the sum of two digits is greater than 9, a carry should be generated and added to the next digit.
The returned linked list should have the most significant digit at the beginning.
The returned linked list should not have any leading zeros.
The length of the returned linked list should be equal to the length of the longer input linked list plus one if a carry is generated.